Charlotte Nikoi went missing on Human Rights Day during a hike on Table Mountain. JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma has urged members of the public to contact the police if they have any information about missing Unicef director Charlotte Nikoi. Nikoi is reported to have arrived in Cape Town on 17 March 2017 on holiday and to celebrate her wedding anniversary with her family. She went missing on Human Rights Day during a hike on Table Mountain. A Ghanaian national, Nikoi is a Unicef director based in New York. President Zuma received a special envoy sent by the president of the republic of Ghana, his excellency President Nana Akufo-Addo, on the sidelines of the World Economic Forum on Africa meeting in Durban, with a special plea for assistance to find Nikoi. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)